    <div class="w-100">
        <h1 class="mb-0">StackOverflow
            <span class="text-primary">Exchange</span>
        </h1>
        <span class="d-block d-lg-none">Stack Rest User Fetcher</span>
        <div class="subheading mb-5" style="width: 80%;margin: 0 auto">
            <h2>Instructions:</h2>
            <p class="lead mb-5">In order to see the users go to next link: <span style="font-weight: bold;">localhost:8080/pages/{count}</span>
                where {count} must be number of pages requested to be processed.
                Keep in mind that every page contains 100 items and stackoverflow has
                throttling policy that can block your ip in case of big amount of requested pages.</p>
            <h2>Requirements: </h2>
            <p class="lead mb-5">Retrieve the list of stack overflow users meeting the following criteria:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>"I. Are located in Romania or Moldova.</li>
                <li>"II. Have a reputation of min 223 points.</li>
                <li>"III. Answered min 1 question.</li>
                <li>"IV. Have the tags: "java",".net","docker" or "C#".</li>
            </ul>
            <h4 style="color: red">Warrning: </h4>
            <p class="lead mb-5">When page <span style="font-weight: bold;">localhost:8080/pages/{count}</span> loads there will be as many calls to stack overflow api as was indicated in {count} parameter</p>
        </div>

    </div>

</div>
